author: The Associated Press
description: Philippine President Rodrigo Duterte declared the country's south under martial rule for 60 days.
title: Duterte declares martial rule in south Philippines amid deadly clashes

author: Felipe Villamor
description: President Rodrigo Duterte stressed that the campaign to defeat Islamic State-linked militants on a southern island would be “harsh.”
title: Duterte Calls on Philippines to Support His Declaration of Martial Law

author: Frances Martel
description: Philippines President Rodrigo Duterte has threatened to expand a 60-day state of emergency in southern Mindanao to the whole country.
title: Duterte Says 'Spare No One' as Islamic State Beheads Police Chief, Stages Mass Prison Break

author: Shaun Walker
description: Rodrigo Duterte embarks on five-day visit as he seeks to loosen ties with Washington and strengthen bond with Russia
title: Philippine president Duterte flies to Moscow to meet 'hero' Putin

author: Nyshka Chandran
description: Philippine President Rodrigo Duterte's hint of nationwide martial law has triggered fears of further human rights violations.
title: Philippines: Duterte's talk of martial law sparks fresh human rights worries

description: The Latest on the siege of a Philippine city that led President Rodrigo Duterte to declare martial law in the south (all times local):
title: The Latest: Duterte considering nationwide martial law

author: Al Jazeera
description: Ongoing violence prompts 'mass exodus' from Marawi, a day after Philippine leader Rodrigo Duterte declared martial law.
title: Mindanao: Churchgoers 'taken hostage' amid Marawi siege

author: Felipe Villamor
description: The military fought rebels and deployed tanks in the besieged city of Marawi. The chaos has led President Rodrigo Duterte to impose martial law in the country’s south.
title: Battle in Philippines With ISIS-Linked Militants Is Test for Duterte

author: Euan McKirdy, Joshua Berlinger, CNN
description: Philippines President Rodrigo Duterte said his martial law declaration for the country's restive south could be expanded "throughout the country" in order to combat the rise of ISIS.
title: Duterte says he may expand martial law 'throughout the country' in fight against ISIS

author: Reuters Editorial
description: United States President Donald Trump praised Philippine President Rodrigo Duterte for doing an "unbelievable job on the drug problem" during a phone conversation last month, the New York Times reported, quoting a transcript of the call.
title: Trump praises Duterte for an 'unbelievable job' on drug issue: New York Times
